1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,036
Here's the trap most developers fall into.

2
00:00:03,986 --> 00:00:08,697
They learn the WHAT of A P I Gateway but never the WHY.

3
00:00:08,697 --> 00:00:17,855
They can tell you what it does but not why it exists, what problem it solves, or what happens when it fails.

4
00:00:17,855 --> 00:00:19,723
And that gap?

5
00:00:19,723 --> 00:00:23,236
That's exactly where interviewers live.

6
00:00:23,236 --> 00:00:30,210
Real talk: I've seen senior engineers at Amazon get this wrong in interviews.

7
00:00:30,210 --> 00:00:32,605
Don't be that person.

